16:23.149 --> 16:25.650
Who's hungry?

16:33.125 --> 16:34.692
[ Cellphone bloops ]

16:35.961 --> 16:37.929
[ Cellphone clicks ]

16:37.931 --> 16:41.099
[ Sighs ]

16:48.941 --> 16:52.844
♪♪

17:08.727 --> 17:10.762
[ Sobs ]

17:22.141 --> 17:24.909
[ Breathes shakily ]

17:27.413 --> 17:30.448
[ Sighs ]

17:36.688 --> 17:39.390
Woman: [ Through cellphone ]
<i>Today, I feel good.</i>

17:39.392 --> 17:43.094
<i>Nothing stands between me</i>
<i>and my best me but...</i>

17:43.096 --> 17:44.595
[ Cellphone thuds ]

17:50.869 --> 17:54.806
♪♪

17:57.943 --> 17:59.243
[ Grunts ]

17:59.245 --> 18:00.945
[ Handle rattles ]

18:04.249 --> 18:07.585
Hi, Susan, it's Le...

18:07.587 --> 18:09.420
Look, I'm kind of in a rush.

18:09.422 --> 18:11.189
What's the code
to the mini bar?

18:11.191 --> 18:12.723
I'm sorry.

18:12.725 --> 18:14.459
Javi-eh told us
- He didn't want either of you

18:14.461 --> 18:15.827
to have the code.

18:16.462 --> 18:17.995
[ Receiver slams ]

18:23.535 --> 18:25.036
[ Clatter ]

18:30.976 --> 18:33.478
Excuse me. Hi.

18:33.480 --> 18:34.979
Hi. Help you?

18:34.981 --> 18:36.747
If you give me the code
to open my mini bar,

18:36.749 --> 18:38.082
you will definitely help me.

18:38.084 --> 18:40.551
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6.

18:40.553 --> 18:42.120
Fort Knox, huh?

18:42.122 --> 18:43.955
Same for all the rooms.

18:43.957 --> 18:46.624
It's not like they want to make
it hard to get to the booze.

18:46.626 --> 18:48.726
High five.

18:48.728 --> 18:51.295
[ Buttons beeping ]

18:51.297 --> 18:52.663
[ Loud beep ]

18:55.334 --> 18:56.701
[ Bottles clinking ]

19:09.481 --> 19:09.981
♪♪

19:27.199 --> 19:28.599
Daniela:
It's short for Leticia.

19:28.601 --> 19:29.800
Is she black?

19:29.802 --> 19:32.036
Oh, my God, Mom,
you're so racist.

19:32.038 --> 19:34.305
Not everything is racist.

19:34.307 --> 19:35.773
What does she write?

19:35.775 --> 19:37.008
She hasn't
published anything yet.

19:37.010 --> 19:38.342
She's writing this book
about a guy

19:38.344 --> 19:40.111
who looks exactly like
Ryan Gosling,

19:40.113 --> 19:42.480
so he pretends to be him
to make it in Hollywood.

19:42.482 --> 19:44.182
And then it's like a thriller
or something.

19:44.184 --> 19:46.817
Yeah, for her real job,
she works at Instagram.

19:46.819 --> 19:49.787
Wow. What does she do
at Instagram?

19:51.323 --> 19:53.324
I don't know.

19:53.326 --> 19:54.492
You don't know?

19:54.494 --> 19:55.860
Is she a real person?

19:55.862 --> 19:58.629
Relax, Mom.
They just started dating.

19:58.631 --> 20:00.298
I need proof.

20:00.300 --> 20:01.666
Show me a picture.

20:01.668 --> 20:02.833
I don't have one.

20:02.835 --> 20:05.002
You don't have
a picture of her?

20:05.004 --> 20:06.671
It's new. It's a new thing.
I don't have one.

20:06.673 --> 20:08.940
So text her and ask for one.

20:10.042 --> 20:11.842
[ Laughing ] Come on!

20:11.844 --> 20:15.079
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

20:21.486 --> 20:22.687
[ Cellphone camera clicks ]

20:22.689 --> 20:24.922
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

20:26.491 --> 20:29.994
Here.

20:31.029 --> 20:33.864
Oh, she's gorgeous.

20:33.866 --> 20:36.934
Wait, that doesn't
look like her.

20:36.936 --> 20:38.035
Sofia: Yeah, yeah.
- It's her.

20:38.037 --> 20:39.270
She's wearing a wig.

20:39.272 --> 20:41.339
Is she sick?

20:41.341 --> 20:43.741
What do you mean?
I mean, like, cancer.

20:43.743 --> 20:45.376
No, she likes to wear wigs.

20:45.378 --> 20:46.611
She knows what's up.

20:46.613 --> 20:49.413
I read this thing about how wigs
are like the new purses.

20:49.415 --> 20:50.948
Like, it's part of your outfit.

20:50.950 --> 20:52.283
Okay.
[ Chuckles ]

20:52.285 --> 20:55.820
Can we please talk now, Ava?

20:57.256 --> 20:59.390
Okay. Let's go.

20:59.392 --> 21:01.325
Where are we going?
We'll talk when we get there.

21:01.327 --> 21:03.027
Girls, stay here and clean up.

21:03.029 --> 21:04.395
Sofia:
Isn't Soledad here?

21:04.397 --> 21:06.230
She's watching TV.

21:06.232 --> 21:08.699
I'm not doing this by myself.

21:08.701 --> 21:09.734
Daniela: Really?

21:09.736 --> 21:10.801
Yeah, really.

21:10.803 --> 21:14.005
[ Slot machine chirping ]

21:15.707 --> 21:16.907
Man: [ In distance ] Yeah!

21:16.909 --> 21:18.409
[ Slot machine chirping ]

21:18.411 --> 21:20.344
Woman:
Martini on the house?

21:23.815 --> 21:25.883
[ Southern accent ] I'm okay.

21:35.093 --> 21:38.396
[ Slot machine chirping ]

21:44.436 --> 21:45.569
Actually, wait.

21:58.583 --> 22:01.285
Don't you hate it when people
only pour halfway?

22:01.287 --> 22:03.454
What's the rest of the glass
for?

22:03.456 --> 22:04.955
Guilt and optimism.

22:04.957 --> 22:07.458
[ Laughs ]

22:07.460 --> 22:09.126
♪♪

22:09.128 --> 22:12.129
I really shouldn't be here.
I shouldn't.

22:12.131 --> 22:13.297
But I just can't help myself

22:13.299 --> 22:14.832
when it comes
to beautiful things.

22:14.834 --> 22:16.133
Well, I always say

22:16.135 --> 22:18.169
beautiful things
- Deserve beautiful things.

22:18.171 --> 22:20.771
But that's just
what I say.
- I love that.

22:20.773 --> 22:22.340
And this.

22:22.342 --> 22:24.141
Well, you have very good taste.

22:24.143 --> 22:26.510
Can I be honest with you,
George?
- Of course.

22:26.512 --> 22:28.779
So, my husband...
He's in the dog house.

22:28.781 --> 22:30.614
And sometimes
his only ticket out

22:30.616 --> 22:31.716
is with a little bling.

22:31.718 --> 22:32.950
Know what I mean?

22:32.952 --> 22:34.685
How bad was he?

22:34.687 --> 22:36.487
Real bad.

22:36.489 --> 22:37.955
Four carats bad?

22:37.957 --> 22:40.224
More like 15-carats-flawless
despicable.

22:40.226 --> 22:41.192
[ Chuckles ]

22:41.194 --> 22:43.894
A little more champs?

22:47.032 --> 22:48.499
Oh, wait, where's
- The double heart platinum

22:48.501 --> 22:50.868
you just showed me?
Oh, that's...

22:50.870 --> 22:53.337
Well,
it was right here.
- Oh.

22:53.339 --> 22:55.740
Did I put that away
- When I pulled out the sapphire?

22:55.742 --> 22:57.541
Oh, here it is...

22:58.477 --> 23:01.979
right under this box.

23:01.981 --> 23:04.482
A little more champagne?

23:04.484 --> 23:05.583
Of course.

23:10.989 --> 23:12.823
Well, what do we think?

23:12.825 --> 23:14.358
Oh, this one for sure.

23:14.360 --> 23:16.727
When my husband
- Gets off the golf course,

23:16.729 --> 23:18.329
I will send him in here,

23:18.331 --> 23:20.831
and you steer him right to
that double heart platinum.

23:20.833 --> 23:22.500
Deal?

23:22.502 --> 23:23.601
Deal.

23:24.035 --> 23:25.536
Bye, George.

23:25.538 --> 23:27.371
Bye, Brittany.

23:27.373 --> 23:30.474
♪♪

23:57.402 --> 24:00.504
♪♪

24:27.466 --> 24:30.568
♪♪

24:38.643 --> 24:41.846
The first step is admitting
you have a problem, right?

24:41.848 --> 24:44.949
[ Chuckles ]

24:44.951 --> 24:46.484
Right.

24:48.787 --> 24:51.121
One time I won $200.

24:51.123 --> 24:52.623
That was 11 years ago,

24:52.625 --> 24:55.025
and I've been feeding
this hungry beast ever since.

24:55.027 --> 24:57.695
I even got tennis elbow.

24:59.197 --> 25:01.332
Slots aren't usually my thing.

25:01.334 --> 25:03.467
I'm more of a poker guy, so...

25:03.469 --> 25:06.504
Well, what are you doing
sitting here, then?

25:06.506 --> 25:09.139
Or is it just my lucky day?

25:09.141 --> 25:11.208
It's more like my lucky day.
[ Chuckles ]

25:11.210 --> 25:13.110
I mean, you're very...

25:13.112 --> 25:15.980
I... I don't usually
meet women like you.

25:15.982 --> 25:17.648
Why not?

25:17.650 --> 25:20.818
I'm not really in your league.

25:20.820 --> 25:24.522
Bullshit.
I decide that.

25:24.524 --> 25:26.190
What's your name?

25:27.325 --> 25:29.293
It's, uh... It's Jeff.

25:29.295 --> 25:31.462
Well, I decide that, Jeff.

25:31.464 --> 25:34.098
And you<i> are</i> in my league.

25:36.501 --> 25:38.068
Wow. Uh...

25:38.070 --> 25:39.303
Do...
uh, do you want to...

25:39.305 --> 25:40.704
Should we get a drink, or...?

25:40.706 --> 25:42.740
I don't drink.

25:42.742 --> 25:44.008
Oh. Sorry.

25:44.010 --> 25:45.175
No, don't be sorry.

25:45.177 --> 25:46.544
How would you know?

25:46.546 --> 25:47.978
[ Sighs ] Right.

25:47.980 --> 25:51.015
But I'm going to the spa
in a minute to get a facial.

25:51.017 --> 25:52.416
You free later tonight?

25:52.418 --> 25:53.384
Yeah.

25:53.386 --> 25:55.152
I mean, yeah,
I'm staying here, so...

25:55.154 --> 25:57.855
Great.

25:57.857 --> 26:00.791
Give me your phone.
I'll give you my number.

26:01.793 --> 26:03.227
Yeah, okay.

26:06.765 --> 26:08.866
Oh, what's your passcode?

26:08.868 --> 26:12.336
Uh, it's, uh, 7273.

26:18.710 --> 26:19.910
[ Chuckles ]

26:19.912 --> 26:22.379
Stupid auto-correct.

26:22.381 --> 26:24.048
I know how to spell
my own name.

26:24.050 --> 26:26.450
[ Both chuckle ]

26:32.223 --> 26:34.058
That's me.

26:34.060 --> 26:35.793
Juliette Lewis?

26:35.795 --> 26:38.896
I know.
I'm the other one.
[ Chuckles ]

26:38.898 --> 26:40.998
Text me later.

26:44.202 --> 26:47.471
♪♪

26:53.712 --> 26:56.080
Hi. We're staying
with you tonight,

26:56.082 --> 26:57.481
and I was just wondering

26:57.483 --> 26:59.917
what's the earliest
we can check in?

26:59.919 --> 27:02.453
It's under Sanderson.

27:03.655 --> 27:04.655
4:00.

27:04.657 --> 27:07.691
Great.
I'll see you then.

27:12.097 --> 27:14.665
Christian:
- [ Slurring ] I did not make
any trouble for you!

27:14.667 --> 27:16.734
Bartender:
- Security is on their way.

27:16.736 --> 27:18.969
Ah, maybe you never
spilled anything.

27:18.971 --> 27:21.438
Congratulations.

27:21.440 --> 27:23.140
No, no, I mean it.

27:23.142 --> 27:24.608
Good for you.

27:24.610 --> 27:26.510
Christian?

27:28.680 --> 27:31.949
My favorite client.
New hair.

27:31.951 --> 27:33.851
Did you follow me?

27:33.853 --> 27:35.285
Of course not.

27:35.287 --> 27:37.021
I come to the Riverhouse Café
all the time... Resort.

27:37.023 --> 27:39.289
Hey. Hey. I got him.
I got him. I got him.
Man: Let's go.

27:39.291 --> 27:40.324
It's okay.

27:40.326 --> 27:42.459
Okay, come on.

27:42.461 --> 27:44.695
Come on. Let's go.

27:46.131 --> 27:48.432
Jesus, Christian.
Come on.
Christian: [ Laughs ]

27:51.536 --> 27:53.537
Letty: No, no, no, no, no, no.
Don't lay down.

27:53.539 --> 27:55.339
You have to sit up.

27:55.341 --> 27:56.940
Can we get a couple of coffees?

27:56.942 --> 27:58.776
Is he gonna be
a problem?
- No.

27:58.778 --> 28:00.944
Because you can
clean up the vomit.

28:00.946 --> 28:02.646
Won't be the first time.

28:02.648 --> 28:05.382
[ Indistinct conversations ]

28:05.384 --> 28:06.884
Christian!

28:08.053 --> 28:10.554
You followed me to Savannah?

28:10.556 --> 28:11.622
Wow.

28:11.624 --> 28:13.057
Wow.

28:13.059 --> 28:17.728
Look, I'm sorry,
- But I don't want to fuck you.

28:17.730 --> 28:19.897
You're so arrogant.

28:19.899 --> 28:21.665
So you didn't come here
to fuck me?

28:21.667 --> 28:23.200
No, I didn't come here
to fuck you.

28:23.202 --> 28:28.072
I have 24 hours to find you
and send you back to prison.

28:28.074 --> 28:30.808
But it only took me six.

28:32.410 --> 28:34.311
Impressive.

28:34.313 --> 28:35.546
How'd you do it?

28:51.096 --> 28:52.429
I meant to do that.

28:52.431 --> 28:55.099
[ Chuckles ]
Cry for help?
- Apparently.

28:55.101 --> 28:57.000
Glad I can be there for you.

28:57.002 --> 29:00.304
[ Indistinct conversations ]

29:02.674 --> 29:04.341
Christian, what the hell?

29:04.343 --> 29:05.442
What is this?

29:05.444 --> 29:08.378
I have the same question
about this coffee.

29:08.380 --> 29:12.116
[ Coughs ] Why are you drunk?

29:12.118 --> 29:14.351
Because I didn't want
to come here.

29:14.353 --> 29:16.787
I don't want to have to
turn you in.

29:16.789 --> 29:18.122
Then don't.

29:18.124 --> 29:20.390
I'll get fired.
Then turn me in.

29:20.392 --> 29:21.792
Do whatever you want to do.

29:21.794 --> 29:23.060
But you might want to wait

29:23.062 --> 29:24.728
until you stop
slurring your words.

29:24.730 --> 29:27.097
Why are you here?

29:27.899 --> 29:30.467
Oh, this really does
taste like shit.

29:30.469 --> 29:33.637
You have violated your parole
so many...

29:33.639 --> 29:34.805
You know what it means

29:34.807 --> 29:36.406
not to show up
for your check-in?

29:36.408 --> 29:38.475
My reunion was a shit show.

29:38.477 --> 29:39.643
I needed a vacation.

29:39.645 --> 29:41.111
[ Slams table ]

29:41.113 --> 29:43.147
Why are you doing this
to me?!
- To you?

29:43.149 --> 29:44.681
[ Bangs table ]

29:46.384 --> 29:47.551
I'm sorry.

29:51.656 --> 29:53.957
Tell me.

29:59.063 --> 30:02.833
Okay, I wanted to come back
and tell you I got a job,

30:02.835 --> 30:06.403
a place to live, and Jacob.

30:11.609 --> 30:15.479
I have this thing
going with my mom.

30:15.481 --> 30:16.513
I give her $1,000,

30:16.515 --> 30:18.916
and she lets me
spend a day with him.

30:18.918 --> 30:21.084
No shit?

30:22.687 --> 30:25.189
I thought I could
try and make a life there

30:25.191 --> 30:28.158
and keep it going, but I can't.

30:28.160 --> 30:30.160
I can't be there.

30:30.162 --> 30:32.963
Why are you dressed like this?

30:32.965 --> 30:36.200
I look good.
- You look great.

30:36.202 --> 30:38.202
Hmm. And you look like
absolute shit.

30:38.204 --> 30:41.038
So which would you
rather talk about?

30:41.040 --> 30:43.207
Still you.
The wig, the clothes...

30:43.209 --> 30:47.544
When I want to get high...

30:47.546 --> 30:48.545
When I want to get high,

30:48.547 --> 30:50.480
the only thing
to replace that need

30:50.482 --> 30:52.883
is doing other crazy shit.

30:52.885 --> 30:54.151
Like stealing.

30:54.153 --> 30:56.119
I'm familiar
with your rap sheet.

30:56.121 --> 30:59.690
So like an hour ago,
I stole a $20,000 ring.

30:59.692 --> 31:01.391
But I didn't buy drugs.

31:01.393 --> 31:04.394
I didn't get high.
I didn't drink.

31:04.396 --> 31:06.296
Well, I had
a few sips of champagne,

31:06.298 --> 31:07.664
but that was part of it.

31:07.666 --> 31:09.700
Part of<i> what?</i>

31:09.702 --> 31:11.668
Brittany.

31:11.670 --> 31:15.138
The woman I was pretending to be
with the sales guy.

31:15.140 --> 31:17.074
That's half the high...

31:17.076 --> 31:18.475
pretending, dressing up.

31:18.477 --> 31:20.644
Can't you just
go to the movies?

31:20.646 --> 31:23.347
Movies aren't good anymore.
Or a meeting?

31:23.349 --> 31:26.917
An A.A. meeting?
No. Not my thing.

31:26.919 --> 31:28.085
Me, neither,

31:28.087 --> 31:30.554
but neither
is breaking the law.

31:30.556 --> 31:32.589
Oh, slow clap.

31:32.824 --> 31:34.424
[ Sighs ]

31:34.426 --> 31:37.227
Look, I can smoke all
the meth in the world
and kill myself,

31:37.229 --> 31:39.930
or I can dress up,
steal some shit,

31:39.932 --> 31:42.266
and not kill myself.

31:42.268 --> 31:44.735
Speaking of which,
I have to go.

31:44.737 --> 31:48.405
You're not telling me that
you're going to steal...
The opposite.

31:48.407 --> 31:50.407
On my way out of
the hotel jewelry store,

31:50.409 --> 31:53.176
I thought the security guy
was gonna nail me for the ring.

31:53.178 --> 31:55.279
I watched him very carefully

31:55.281 --> 31:58.615
until I realized
- He gave zero fucks about me.

31:58.617 --> 31:59.950
Long story short,

31:59.952 --> 32:02.319
him and his dumbass friend
are trying to rip off the hotel,

32:02.321 --> 32:03.887
and I'm gonna
try and stop them.

32:03.889 --> 32:06.523
And maybe you'll make off
with the money instead.

32:06.525 --> 32:08.191
Maybe.

32:09.127 --> 32:10.594
You want to help?

32:10.596 --> 32:12.362
[ Chuckles ]

32:15.233 --> 32:16.533
You're serious.

32:16.535 --> 32:18.802
M-Maybe it'll get you high
like it does for me,

32:18.804 --> 32:20.270
and then you'll understand.

32:31.049 --> 32:33.550
Good night, Victor.
Thanks, Mike.

33:44.889 --> 33:48.191
♪♪

34:00.405 --> 34:03.907
♪ You got me feelin'
like I did before ♪

34:04.475 --> 34:07.477
♪ Only to know
I can't take no more ♪

34:07.912 --> 34:11.648
♪ You got me
shakin' and everything ♪

34:11.650 --> 34:15.519
♪ You got me breathin'
like I did again ♪

34:15.521 --> 34:18.822
♪ Ah-ah-ah-ah, ah, ah-ah ♪

34:19.157 --> 34:23.093
♪ Ah-ah-ah-ah, ah, ah-ah ♪

34:23.095 --> 34:24.761
♪ And then I dream ♪

34:24.763 --> 34:27.531
♪ And I know
it's coming closer ♪

34:27.533 --> 34:28.932
♪♪

34:28.934 --> 34:31.401
Christian: This man
is much older than me.

34:31.403 --> 34:33.403
Keep telling yourself that.

34:33.405 --> 34:35.405
But the room
is under Sanderson,

34:35.407 --> 34:37.741
and this guy's name
is Trey Edward.

34:37.743 --> 34:38.942
Edwards. With an "S."

34:38.944 --> 34:40.277
Edwards. Fine.

34:40.279 --> 34:42.112
Which still isn't Sanderson.

34:42.114 --> 34:43.380
It's so easy.

34:43.382 --> 34:45.115
Here's what you do.

34:45.117 --> 34:46.416
Susan: Can we help you
with any bags?

34:46.418 --> 34:49.519
No. No.
It's, uh, just one night.

34:49.521 --> 34:52.122
Oh, you travel light.
Uh, no baggage fees.

34:52.124 --> 34:53.790
[ Both laugh ]

35:03.601 --> 35:05.602
Mr. Sanderson,
- I just need a driver's license

35:05.604 --> 35:07.804
and credit card
for incidentals.
- Here you go.

35:08.039 --> 35:09.106
I'm sorry.

35:09.108 --> 35:10.307
This is a different name

35:10.309 --> 35:12.109
than we have
on the reservation.

35:12.111 --> 35:14.644
Yes.
- Sanderson is my stage name.

35:14.646 --> 35:18.315
Your stage name?
Uh, not a stage name.

35:18.317 --> 35:20.317
It's the opposite.

35:20.319 --> 35:23.120
It's the name I use
to check in to hotels

35:23.122 --> 35:25.255
and to make dinner reservations

35:25.257 --> 35:28.158
because I'm an actor.

35:28.160 --> 35:30.127
I'm sorry.
I don't recognize you.

35:30.129 --> 35:31.795
I'm sort of famous.

35:31.797 --> 35:33.130
I just don't have
that much time

35:33.132 --> 35:34.297
to go to the movies
or watch TV.

35:34.299 --> 35:35.799
Me, neither.
[ Both laugh ]

35:35.801 --> 35:37.300
Letty: Trey Edwards?

35:37.302 --> 35:39.503
Oh, my God,
- I am so sorry to bother you.

35:39.505 --> 35:41.671
I just had to see
if it was really you.

35:41.673 --> 35:44.407
Okay...
"NCIS" is my all-time
favorite show.

35:44.409 --> 35:46.343
Oh.
- Since
the very beginning.

35:46.345 --> 35:48.078
Especially since you're on it.

35:48.080 --> 35:50.780
They should have you on it more,
though, don't you think?

35:50.782 --> 35:52.516
I do.

35:52.518 --> 35:53.917
Can we take a picture?

35:53.919 --> 35:55.085
No, I don't really...

35:55.087 --> 35:56.486
Will you take our picture?

35:56.488 --> 35:58.355
Aren't you the one
with Ava's brother?

35:58.357 --> 35:59.856
Good eye, girl.

35:59.858 --> 36:02.859
I wouldn't think you'd
recognize me with my new hair.

36:03.694 --> 36:05.195
Thank you.

36:05.197 --> 36:06.197
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

36:06.198 --> 36:07.531
[ Groans ]

36:07.533 --> 36:09.366
I think I'm gonna throw up.

36:09.368 --> 36:10.500
Relax. It worked.

36:10.502 --> 36:11.968
Oh, it was a mess.

36:11.970 --> 36:13.270
I'm<i> not</i> doing this.

36:13.272 --> 36:14.704
Christian, you were fine.
You had her.

36:14.706 --> 36:16.206
I was just
speeding things along

36:16.208 --> 36:17.507
because we don't
have much time.

36:17.509 --> 36:19.609
Until what?
- 4:30.

36:19.611 --> 36:22.312
What's happening at 4:30?
Oh, you are so annoying.

36:22.314 --> 36:23.713
We've been over this.
- Uh-huh.

36:23.715 --> 36:25.148
Something to do with room 520.

36:25.150 --> 36:27.384
I don't know exactly what,
but that's the fun part.

36:27.386 --> 36:28.718
[ Sighs ]

36:28.720 --> 36:30.887
Stand up straight.
Woman:<i> Fifth floor.</i>

36:32.723 --> 36:35.859
♪♪

36:45.703 --> 36:46.803
Hi.

36:46.805 --> 36:48.505
I recognize you.

36:48.507 --> 36:51.708
You helped me with my
little mini bar crisis.

36:51.710 --> 36:53.476
[ Chuckles ] Yes, ma'am.

36:53.478 --> 36:54.911
So you're a security guy
<i>and</i> a waiter?

36:54.913 --> 36:56.379
Well, I split the shifts.

36:56.381 --> 36:57.514
Extra money.
- Oh.

36:57.516 --> 36:59.049
You know what I call that?

36:59.051 --> 37:00.784
I call that a Renaissance man.

37:01.319 --> 37:03.720
Okay.
- Okay.

37:08.326 --> 37:09.459
Room service.

37:12.897 --> 37:14.197
[ Door lock beeps ]

37:14.199 --> 37:16.499
There's no one in that room.

37:17.501 --> 37:20.937
Okay, so, what do we do now?

37:22.240 --> 37:23.740
Now we go to our room.

37:25.443 --> 37:26.676
[ Door lock beeps ]

37:26.678 --> 37:29.746
♪♪

37:36.087 --> 37:37.621
What are you doing?
I don't know.

37:37.623 --> 37:38.888
Is it safe?
- Close the door.

37:38.890 --> 37:40.991
I don't care what side
you end up on.

37:46.364 --> 37:48.765
I have a theory.
- Okay.

37:48.767 --> 37:50.767
So, they're updating
the ATM machines

37:50.769 --> 37:52.369
around the hotel.

37:52.371 --> 37:53.536
While they update the machines,

37:53.538 --> 37:54.704
the money has to go somewhere,

37:54.706 --> 37:56.906
so they hide it in a room.

37:56.908 --> 37:59.442
Those room-service carts
are full of the money.

37:59.444 --> 38:01.211
So, what are we doing
in this room?

38:01.213 --> 38:03.947
Because these guys are doing
a dumb, little inside job.

38:03.949 --> 38:07.250
The guy whose phone I grabbed
is probably gonna get the money

38:07.252 --> 38:09.319
from his
- Security guard/waiter friend

38:09.321 --> 38:11.721
and bring it
to this room.
- Why?

38:11.723 --> 38:13.790
So the cameras don't pick him up
when he's leaving the hotel.

38:13.792 --> 38:16.059
There's cameras
in every hallway.

38:16.061 --> 38:19.296
They disabled the ones
on this floor earlier today.

38:19.298 --> 38:20.897
You have a gun
around your calf, right?

38:20.899 --> 38:22.098
[ Lock disengages,
beeps ]
Yes.

38:22.100 --> 38:22.899
Shit.

38:26.237 --> 38:27.404
Oh, my God.

38:27.406 --> 38:28.905
Honey, there's someone
in the room.

38:28.907 --> 38:31.641
Uh, I'm sorry.
I-I thought this was my room.

38:31.643 --> 38:33.410
This is obviously our room.

38:33.412 --> 38:34.978
Juliette?

38:37.415 --> 38:39.249
Police.

38:39.251 --> 38:40.583
We know exactly what you did.

38:40.585 --> 38:42.085
Uh, Jesus Christ.

38:42.087 --> 38:43.420
Drop the bag, Jeff.

38:43.422 --> 38:45.088
I...
Drop the bag!

38:45.090 --> 38:46.056
[ Bag thuds ]

38:47.525 --> 38:48.858
Put your hands
against the wall.

38:50.428 --> 38:51.528
Frisk him.

38:57.368 --> 38:58.601
He's clean.

38:58.603 --> 39:00.036
Bring the bag over here.

39:06.277 --> 39:07.844
Ohh. Heavy.

39:08.646 --> 39:10.146
How much money
is in the bag, Jeff?

39:10.148 --> 39:12.682
$200,000...
$211,000.

39:13.150 --> 39:14.684
Open it.

39:24.662 --> 39:25.762
Cuff him.

39:28.632 --> 39:32.035
[ Mouthing ]
I don't have handcuffs.

39:33.671 --> 39:36.806
[ Mouthing ]
Robe belt.
- What?

39:37.975 --> 39:38.708
[ Gun clicks ]

39:39.310 --> 39:41.945
Robe belt.

39:54.825 --> 39:56.793
[ Normal voice ]
Sit in the chair, Jeff.

39:57.895 --> 39:58.762
Sit!

40:03.000 --> 40:04.100
Who are you guys?

40:04.102 --> 40:06.469
Tie him to the chair.
Read him his rights.

40:07.405 --> 40:10.507
[ Normal voice ]
So, you have the right
to remain silent.

40:10.509 --> 40:14.244
Christian:
Anything you say or do can
and will be used against you

40:14.246 --> 40:16.346
in a court of law.

40:16.348 --> 40:18.615
You have the right
to an attorney.

40:18.617 --> 40:20.583
If you cannot afford
one of your own,

40:20.585 --> 40:22.752
one will be assigned to you.

40:22.754 --> 40:25.021
Do you understand your rights
as I've read them to you?

40:25.023 --> 40:26.122
No. I...

40:27.124 --> 40:28.191
Ow.

40:28.193 --> 40:29.993
Take it.

40:30.461 --> 40:32.228
That was pretty good, Jeff.

40:32.230 --> 40:33.863
The one thing they always think

40:33.865 --> 40:36.199
is that the money
left the building.

40:36.201 --> 40:37.400
Jeff: Yeah.

40:37.402 --> 40:38.735
And no one will come
looking for you

40:38.737 --> 40:40.737
except your friend Arnold
tomorrow morning.

40:40.739 --> 40:43.907
I think you guys deserve

40:43.909 --> 40:45.708
a little something to divvy up.

40:45.710 --> 40:49.379
Plus I hate odd numbers,
so here's 11.

40:49.381 --> 40:52.148
Two, four, six, eight.
This is bullshit.

40:52.917 --> 40:55.485
You should be grateful
you're getting anything.

40:55.487 --> 40:57.754
And now I've lost count.

40:57.756 --> 40:59.956
[ Evangelist's
"I Wanna Lift You Up" plays ]

40:59.958 --> 41:02.525
Ten, eleven.

41:02.527 --> 41:05.795
♪♪

41:12.002 --> 41:12.936
Sorry about tonight.

41:12.938 --> 41:14.304
♪ I wanna lift you, yeah ♪

41:14.306 --> 41:16.239
I really do think you're cute.

41:16.241 --> 41:17.941
♪♪

41:17.943 --> 41:19.242
Juliette Lewis.

41:19.244 --> 41:21.511
Shout out. Love her.

41:21.513 --> 41:22.745
Bye, Jeff.

41:22.747 --> 41:25.081
♪ I wanna raise you up ♪

41:25.083 --> 41:26.449
Bye, Jeff.

41:26.451 --> 41:32.956
♪ I wanna know you, yeah,
I wanna know what your name ♪

41:32.958 --> 41:36.659
He had a gun.
It happened fast.

41:36.661 --> 41:40.430
♪ Yeah, now bow down,
you've got me ♪

41:40.432 --> 41:44.467
What the fuck did we just do?

41:44.469 --> 41:46.035
Told you.

41:46.037 --> 41:47.337
Holy shit!

41:47.339 --> 41:49.839
60% me, 40% you.

41:49.841 --> 41:52.275
♪ I wanna raise you now,
I wanna raise you up ♪

41:52.277 --> 41:54.043
No. 50-50.

41:56.847 --> 41:58.281
50-50.

41:58.283 --> 42:02.986
♪ I wanna know you, yeah,
I wanna know what your name ♪

42:02.988 --> 42:06.289
[ Laughs ]

42:06.291 --> 42:07.590
Whoo!

43:56.100 --> 43:58.835
[ Cellphone rings ]

43:58.837 --> 44:02.171
[ Sighs ] [ Cellphone beeps ]

44:02.173 --> 44:03.740
Hi.

44:05.776 --> 44:06.909
Shit.

44:08.979 --> 44:11.014
I'll be right there.

44:11.016 --> 44:12.015
[ Sighs ]

44:12.017 --> 44:13.650
[ Cellphone beeps ]
We have to go.

44:22.526 --> 44:24.460
Bye, Jeff!
- Bye, Jeff!

44:24.462 --> 44:26.195
[ Laughter ]

44:26.197 --> 44:28.197
Bye, Jeff!

44:28.199 --> 44:32.168
That's a $5,000 bottle
of Scotch up there.

44:32.170 --> 44:34.203
Where?
- Up there.

44:34.205 --> 44:36.506
The tall one.
- Never tried it.

44:36.508 --> 44:38.274
Don't want to.
- I do.

44:38.276 --> 44:39.876
Why haven't you?

44:39.878 --> 44:41.477
Well...
[ Clink, splash ]

44:41.479 --> 44:44.113
Ooh! [ Laughs ]

44:44.115 --> 44:47.550
Okay. Okay.

44:47.552 --> 44:49.819
Christian.
- Mm.

44:49.821 --> 44:51.454
I think it's time
for you to admit

44:51.456 --> 44:54.023
that your life
has become unmanageable.

44:54.025 --> 44:57.060
You know, you're right.
You're right.

44:57.062 --> 44:58.995
I know I am.

44:58.997 --> 45:01.798
Hi, my name is Christian,
and I'm an alcoholic.

45:01.800 --> 45:05.968
Hi, Christian.
- I have
- negative two hours sober.

45:05.970 --> 45:08.237
Well, you've come
to the right bar.

45:08.239 --> 45:09.639
Do you happen to know

45:09.641 --> 45:12.742
if there's some kind of,
like, power,

45:12.744 --> 45:14.911
one that could
restore my sanity.

45:14.913 --> 45:16.746
Whoa. Wait.
You're insane?

45:16.748 --> 45:18.881
Yeah, I've completely
lost my mind.

45:18.883 --> 45:21.751
Have you tried
- Turning your will and your life

45:21.753 --> 45:24.187
over to the great ghost
in the sky?

45:24.189 --> 45:27.757
Why would I let
- An invisible floating thing...

45:27.759 --> 45:30.693
[ Laughing ]
In the sky...
- ...ln the sky

45:30.695 --> 45:32.729
make all my decisions for me?

45:32.731 --> 45:35.098
Well, your best thinking
got you here.

45:35.100 --> 45:37.166
[ Laughter ]

45:37.168 --> 45:39.769
I saw you spilled.
Freshie on the house.

45:39.771 --> 45:42.238
Christian:
Oh, thank you.
Mm-hmm.

45:44.742 --> 45:46.109
FYI?

45:46.111 --> 45:49.612
The "here" your best thinking
got you to is this bar,

45:49.614 --> 45:54.684
richer than you were
a few hours ago by $100,000.

45:55.519 --> 45:56.786
Man: Excuse me.

45:56.788 --> 45:59.255
[ Sighs ] I'm gonna
buy that bottle.

45:59.257 --> 46:00.556
Don't buy it.

46:00.558 --> 46:02.391
If you really want it,
we can steal it.

46:02.393 --> 46:04.327
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

46:07.464 --> 46:10.266
It seems like
it would be cleaner

46:10.268 --> 46:12.802
just to buy it.

46:12.804 --> 46:15.471
I mean, that's the point
of having money, right?

46:15.473 --> 46:17.974
No.
- Then what's the point?

46:17.976 --> 46:22.545
Getting things you really want
but you can't steal.

46:24.281 --> 46:25.448
Like my son.

46:25.450 --> 46:26.883
For good.

46:28.786 --> 46:31.954
You can't buy your son
from your mom.

46:33.223 --> 46:36.459
Oh. I guess you can.

46:36.461 --> 46:39.428
I know what you should buy.

46:39.430 --> 46:41.063
You d-yeah?

46:41.065 --> 46:41.664
Your freedom.

46:41.666 --> 46:44.901
My freedom.

46:44.903 --> 46:46.969
You really think
I'm that miserable.

46:46.971 --> 46:48.838
Kinda. Yeah.

46:48.840 --> 46:51.908
You never have to go back
to your stupid job

46:51.910 --> 46:53.409
with stupid Gary...

46:53.411 --> 46:54.677
Not ever again.

46:54.679 --> 46:56.679
You don't have to
try to get losers

46:56.681 --> 46:58.481
to stop being losers anymore.

46:58.483 --> 46:59.849
You calling yourself a loser?

46:59.851 --> 47:01.517
I'm not a loser.
I'm awesome.

47:01.519 --> 47:03.653
You are.

47:05.823 --> 47:08.691
[ Sighs ]
What the hell would I do?

47:08.693 --> 47:11.694
Whatever you want.

47:11.696 --> 47:13.696
I just hope
I don't have to take

47:13.698 --> 47:15.932
a fearless moral inventory
of myself.

47:15.934 --> 47:17.633
I really don't want to do that.

47:17.635 --> 47:19.702
That's the addict talking.

47:19.704 --> 47:21.270
You're a good guy.

47:22.172 --> 47:24.006
Even if you are a stalker.

47:24.008 --> 47:25.541
[ Laughs ]

47:25.543 --> 47:27.109
Javier: Letty.

47:27.878 --> 47:29.378
Look who's breaking the rules.

47:29.380 --> 47:30.646
Hey.

47:30.648 --> 47:32.014
As long as you know the rules,

47:32.016 --> 47:33.950
you can break them
every once in a while.

47:33.952 --> 47:36.552
Hmm.
- Sit down. Sit down.

47:36.554 --> 47:37.887
Is this...

47:37.889 --> 47:41.457
This is the guy I've been,
you know, whatever.

47:41.459 --> 47:43.392
How are you?
Christian.

47:43.394 --> 47:44.660
I've heard a lot abo...

47:44.662 --> 47:46.062
I... actually,
- I haven't heard a lot abo-

47:46.064 --> 47:47.663
It's all been very nebulous.

47:47.665 --> 47:50.533
Probably a good thing.
Letty:
Definitely a good thing.

47:50.535 --> 47:52.301
Christian's my parole officer,
so...

47:52.303 --> 47:54.470
Christian:
<i>Was</i> her parole officer.

47:54.472 --> 47:56.239
I quit.
I'm quitting.

47:56.241 --> 47:57.640
You are?

47:57.642 --> 47:59.175
Either that
or I'm going to get fired.

47:59.177 --> 48:00.977
Whatever comes first.
[ Laughs ]

48:00.979 --> 48:03.913
Hey, I might be here a little
longer than I thought.

48:03.915 --> 48:06.916
Can you go back to the house
and check on the girls?

48:06.918 --> 48:09.518
Javier: Yes.
Of course I can.
You must be Ava.

48:09.520 --> 48:11.053
Letty. Right?
- Yeah.

48:11.055 --> 48:13.356
Without a wig.
Yeah. [ Laughs ]

48:13.358 --> 48:16.592
Obviously the girls
told you everything.
Of course they did.

48:16.594 --> 48:18.427
Good.
I knew he wouldn't.

48:18.429 --> 48:20.663
[ Laughs ] Okay.

48:20.665 --> 48:22.098
I hope I'm not overstepping,

48:22.100 --> 48:24.233
but, Letty,
I'd love you to join us

48:24.235 --> 48:26.736
for a family dinner
we're having next week.

48:26.738 --> 48:30.873
Umm. Yeah. I'd love to.
Great.
- Great.

48:30.875 --> 48:32.375
Javier has all the details.

48:32.377 --> 48:34.443
I'm so sorry,
but I... I have to run.

48:34.445 --> 48:36.946
I had a bit of
a security issue today.

48:36.948 --> 48:38.381
Oh. Oh shit, yeah.

48:38.383 --> 48:39.615
Go. Go.

48:39.617 --> 48:41.484
See you soon.
- See you.

48:42.686 --> 48:44.287
Don't forget the girls.

48:45.022 --> 48:47.023
Do you want to come with me
to the house?

48:47.025 --> 48:48.791
I should probably
stay with Christian.

48:48.793 --> 48:50.459
Uh, n-o, no, no.

48:50.461 --> 48:52.128
Please, go.
I'm good.

48:52.130 --> 48:54.463
Are you sure?
Yeah, I'm sure.

48:54.465 --> 48:56.632
I'm great.
I'm celebrating.

48:56.634 --> 48:58.868
Never stop.

48:58.870 --> 49:00.636
And never stop stalking me.

49:00.638 --> 49:02.371
Don't worry.

49:04.441 --> 49:05.975
Thank you.

49:07.110 --> 49:08.978
Thank you.

49:08.980 --> 49:10.947
What was the security issue?

49:10.949 --> 49:13.549
Someone stole $200,000.

49:13.551 --> 49:15.484
No shit.

49:15.486 --> 49:19.055
$211,000, to be exact.

49:19.057 --> 49:21.123
[ Exhales sharply ]

49:27.998 --> 49:31.300
♪♪
